0 Param data.1 string m_description: A sword crafted by a skilled artisan, though it bears no mark of its maker. Serviceable and sharp.
A sword that honors the royal family of the eastern kingdom. It is infused with energy, raising the health of its wielder.
A sword named after a guardian. Handles well. Excellent for Defense.
A beautiful sword valuable even in its antiquity. Increases starting Affinity.
A sword forged Beyond the Veil that resonates with the souls of the dead. Increases healing (except Incense).
A sword made for slaying Fallen. Favored by many for its offensive power.
A bewitched sword loathed in the Beyond. Increases critical hit chance.
A righteous sword capable of cutting through souls themselves. Increases debuff resistance.
An exquisite sword crafted by a legendary artisan, said to augment one's willpower. Increases Manifest duration.
An ancient, holy sword said to have been crafted by the gods in the Age of Magic. Facilitates gaining Affinity.
A sword as sharp as it is beautiful. Boasts overwhelming offensive power.
A sword crafted by a skilled artisan, though it bears no mark of its maker. Serviceable and sharp.
A spear favored by generations of Blood Guards. Slightly adjustable for easier handling.
Spear from the tale of the betrayer. Its design enhances Defense, perhaps for an advantage in single combat.
A spear wielded by a knight of old, said to have been beloved by the people. Increases health.
A spear symbolic of tragedy in many a tale. Increases debuff resistance.
A spear that enhances healing powers. Also said to bear the ability to grant wishes.
A spear that is the embodiment of valor and nobility. Unmatched in its destructive power.
A spear that births gales in its wake. Increases the strength of jump attacks.
A superb spear tempered in moonlight. Increases Attack in the Beyond, and also increases critical chance.
An unequaled spear forged in sunlight. Increases Attack in the Living World. Also increases critical damage.
A famous spear said to possess the soul of a great king. Dramatically increases Defense when near death.
A spear also known as the Sorcerer's Staff, said to be able to capture shadow. Increases starting Affinity.
A spear favored by generations of Blood Guards. Slightly adjustable for easier handling.
An ingenious axe developed to help the weak stand against the strong. Easily wielded by even the most powerless.
A sentient axe imbued with immense strength, though it's often dormant and rarely unleashes its true potential. Increases critical damage.
An axe forged from a hundred different ores. Increases debuff resistance.
An axe forged on the boundary between worlds. Decreases debuff duration and increases healing (except Incense).
An axe crafted with utmost care by an artisan who became Lost. Infused with the power of life, it increases health.
An axe favored by warriors of old, who fought to the last. Increases chance of debuffing the enemy.
A sturdy axe that will never break. Stories claim it was made to hold the heavens themselves aloft, hence its power.
The beloved axe of a celestial hero. Increases critical chance.
An axe named for a god with earthshaking powers worshipped in the east. Sometimes Staggers the enemy.
The first axe in history made for battle. Can also be used as a hammer. Increases starting Affinity.
An axe that can draw upon the power of the earth itself. Excellent for Defense.
An ingenious axe developed to help the weak stand against the strong. Easily wielded by even the most powerless.
A scythe that severs the dead from their worldly attachments. Those who wield it carry out their task with grim determination.
A scythe excavated from ruins that date back to the early days of the Age of Magic. Increases starting Affinity.
A scythe used in celebratory battle dances, said to have the power to inspire onlookers. Increases health.
A lethal scythe with an intricate blade, capable of dealing wounds that are nearly impossible to recover from.
A scythe that inspires allies and intimidates foes. Excellent for Defense and easy to wield in battle.
A ceremonial scythe used to bless the dead in the Seven-Day Sending. Increases healing (except Incense).
An executioner's scythe, seen as a symbol of justice in some lands. Increases critical chance.
A scythe that reacts to the wielder's thoughts; the purer the thoughts, the more deadly it becomes. Facilitates gaining Affinity.
A scythe born of an oath made between a Watcher and a Daemon. Increases Manifest duration.
A noble scythe that chooses its bearer. It is said to contain a warding power, increasing debuff resistance.
Blades said to bequeath beastlike agility thanks to their ease of use. Favored by many, from soldiers to thieves.
Blades that draw out the hidden strengths of their wielder. Increase health.
Light and sturdy metal blades designed to deflect blows. In the hands of a master they become an impenetrable wall.
Ancient blades stained with blood. Grant a chance to recover health when attacking.
Blades made to kill in one strike, popular for their beauty. Increase critical chance.
Blades created from a toxic liquid turned solid. Each slash introduces poison into the enemy's system. Increase chance of debuffing the enemy.
Blades created in an experiment to combine the advantages of other weapons. Attacks pierce Defense.
Blades discovered in ancient ruins, said to choose their wielder. Increase starting Affinity.
Blades with destructive power far greater than their heft would suggest. Possess offensive might beyond all knowing.
Blades wielded by those who wish to display their prestige. They resonate thought, increasing the power of reflected attacks.
A farshot crafted out of rare ore, economical in design and difficult to break. Once favored by nobility.
A farshot used by battlefield healers. Increases debuff resistance and healing (except Incense).
A cursed farshot said to steal its wielder's good fortune. Increases critical chance.
A precision-engineered farshot constructed with a focus on offensive power.
A farshot consecrated by countless prayers. These blessings bestow great health upon the wielder.
When fired, this farshot emits a beautiful resonance that befuddles the senses. Increases chance of debuffing the enemy.
A farshot that has weathered eternity. Possesses the power to alter a single moment of time. Sometimes Staggers the enemy.
The beloved farshot of a legendary knight. Versatile, but especially suited for Defense.
An assassin's farshot that leaves no trace when fired. Grants chance to instantly kill enemies.
A farshot that represents the will of the people, turning hopes and dreams into raw power. Facilitates gaining Affinity.
A shieldcannon that demonstrated its true power as a siege weapon. Well-balanced between offense and defense.
A shieldcannon that emits a healing pulse, made with drawn-out battles in mind. Increases health.
A shieldcannon that has become the weapon of the devout. Resonates with one's faith to become a defensive bulwark.
A shieldcannon born of the collective knowledge of artillery experts. Increases ranged attack power.
A shieldcannon developed near the end of the Age of Magic after years of research, but never deployed in actual combat. Boasts immense power.
A shieldcannon that absorbs shadow and converts it into raw energy. Increases starting Affinity.
A shieldcannon beloved by a hero in the early years of the Age of Magic. Later modified for a commander. Increases debuff resistance.
A shieldcannon that deals powerful close-range attacks, made to crush all opposition. Sometimes Staggers the enemy.
A shieldcannon excavated from ruins dating back to the early days of the Age of Magic. Increases critical chance.
A shieldcannon from a forbidden continent, crafted using techniques lost to antiquity. Reflects damage when used as a shield.
A fist imbued with chaotic powers. Increases both offensive and defensive abilities.
A fist bearing the boons of countless stars, said to smite with divine strength. Increases critical chance.
A fist that spells doom for the damned. Possesses power enough to kill in a single strike.
A fist that lights the way for those at peace. Its angelic blessing increases Defense and healing (except Incense).
A fist forged at the nexus between dimensions. Possesses mysterious, inviolate power. Increases debuff resistance.
A fist said to hold records of fate dating back to the very beginning. Increases duration of the wielder's buffs.
A fist that reacts to shadow. Emits a prismatic glow in response to its wielder's will. Facilitates gaining Affinity.
A transcendent fist. Legends speak of its indomitable power. Sometimes Staggers the enemy.
A fist that reveals an instant and an eternity are one and the same. Increases Manifest duration.
A miraculous fist coursing with the power of creation. Increases power of attacks while Manifested or Awakened.
A chain crafted by a determined shadowless artisan. Well-made and easy to wield.
A chain capable of twisting a soul in circles and stripping it of its senses. Sometimes Staggers the enemy.
A chain that embodies inner inhibitions. Capable of thwarting attackers. Increases Defense.
A chain that absorbs negative emotions from its surroundings and transforms them into overwhelming power. Facilitates gaining Affinity.
A chain discovered in laboratory ruins from late in the Age of Magic. It rings with the echoes of test subjects' cries. Increases healing (except Incense).
A chain that requires years of training to wield. Mastering it causes one to lose all sense of self. Increases debuff resistance.
A sentient chain that never misses its mark. Increases critical chance.
A chain the shadowless created to fight against the humans they so feared. Crafted with a single-minded focus on offense.
A chain that resonates with—and can even control—one's will, depending on how it's wielded. Increases enemy debuff duration.
A chain crafted by the god of death, or so the stories say. Those bound by it are stripped of ambition. Pierces enemy Defense.
Even a glancing blow from this fang cuts deep. Ferocious and awe-inspiring.
Generations of beasts swore upon this fang that they would protect the land. Increases health.
A fang made to extol dauntless heroes. Affords high defense.
A fang used to consecrate the dead. The prayers bestowed upon it increase the wielder's healing (except Incense).
A fang with an aura of dignity and power. Increases critical chance.
A fang evocative of death itself, said to steep its victims in fear with every attack. Increases chance of debuffing the enemy.
An ominous fang of unknown origin. It's razor sharp and boasts high offensive power.
A fang that can aid its wielder on the path to enlightenment. Increases starting Affinity.
A fang that can only be wielded by those whose hearts are true to the beasts of old. Increases debuff resistance.
A fang that embodies the violence of nature, striking fear into those who witness its power. Increases the wielder's chance of being buffed.
A crystalcore that powered various devices in the Age of Magic. The methods of their crafting are lost to time.
A crystalcore that shines silver when it senses Shadow. Increases critical chance.
A crystalcore born of alchemy, and driven by emotion. Increases max HP and healing (except Incense).
A crystalcore that transmutes the power of nature. Increases chance of debuffing the enemy.
A crystalcore made by converting the purest energy into matter. Increases duration of the wielder's buffs.
A crystalcore crafted from the hardest of metals. Once activated, it cannot be destroyed. Increases Defense.
A crystalcore believed by those of the eastern kingdom to possess eternal power. Increases debuff resistance.
A crystalcore holding myriad thoughts. It emits a strange light when the thoughts within align with those of its wielder. Increases critical hit chance.
A crystalcore forged from legendary ore that amplifies the force of impact, giving it extremely high offensive power.
A crystalcore created by the god of another dimension. Increases Attack based on the number of different skills triggered.
Increases Attack when Affinity is low.
Increases Attack of skill assigned to <ICON=BUTTON_SKILL_1>.
Increases Attack of skill assigned to <ICON=BUTTON_SKILL_2>.
Increases Attack of skill assigned to <ICON=BUTTON_SKILL_3>.
Increases Attack of skill assigned to <ICON=BUTTON_SKILL_4>.
Attacks have a greater chance to stagger, knock back, and cause other hit reactions.
Slight chance to recover HP when attacking. Chance increases when HP is low.
Increases Attack, though you take damage when attacking as well.
Decreases Defense for a massive increase in Attack.
Increases Attack when striking small enemies.
Increases Attack when striking large enemies.
Increases Attack based on the number of buffs in effect.
Increases Attack based on the amount of time that has passed since the previous attack.
Increase the power of attacks based on the number of consecutive skill triggers.
Increases duration of debuffs on enemies.
Allows heals to raise current HP above max HP.
Increases Defense when HP is low.
Increases Defense when Affinity is high.
Puts a cap on damage taken.
Makes it harder to be staggered, knocked back, or suffer other hit reactions.
Grants slight chance to nullify an attack.
Makes you harder to instantly Kill.
Makes you harder for enemies to detect.
Increases precept effects on you in the Beyond.
Decreases precept effects on you in the Beyond.
Makes it possible to invoke precepts from the Beyond in the Living World as well.
